 India win two, lose one in Open
ARIJIT GUHAShanghai: Indian Ladies and Seniors lie on 13th and 11th positions respectively after round 12 of the 38th Bermuda Bowl Bridge Championship on Wednesday. On Day IV of the meet, Indian Open team faced the three top teams (Canada, USA 2 and Poland) of the table, winning two and losing one. Indian Open started off their campaign beating Canada 24-6 VPs. In their second match, they got the better of USA 2 22-8. In USA 2 team Meckstroth and Rodwell played against Pritish Kushari and Debasish Ray in the Closed room, while in the Open, Kamal Roy and Alok Sadhu were pitted against Hamman and Hemant Lall. In the last set against Poland, Pritish and Debasish had a good match in the Open but Kamal Mukherjee and Ashok Goel could not keep up with pace going down 6-24. In Bermuda Bowl, USA 1 lead the chart with 231 VPs, followed by Poland (217) and Italy (212). In the ladies section, USA 1 are again the leaders with 230 VPs, while Germany (216) and France amp; China Global Time (209) lie on second and third spots respectively. Canada with 231 VPs are atop the table in the seniors section, while Italy (228) and USA 1 (213) remain on second and third positions respectively. All the leaders are out of a maximum 300 VPs. 
